1. valuation method(item) 
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”

- It decides how ERPNext calculates the value (cost) of an item in stock when items are purchased, issued, or sold.

default : FIFO

FIFO (First In, First Out)
- The system assumes that the oldest items (first purchased) are sold or issued first.
- For example: You bought 10 units at â‚¹100, and then bought another 10 units at â‚¹120.
- If you sell 10 units, ERPNext will value those issued items at â‚¹100 each, because the first batch purchased is considered sold first.

MA (Moving Average)
- In this method, each new purchase changes the average rate of the item. The issue rate is always the current average rate.
- For example: You bought 10 units at â‚¹100, and then bought another 10 units at â‚¹120.
- The average cost becomes â‚¹110.
- If you sell 5 units, ERPNext will value those issued items at â‚¹110 each, which is the moving average rate.


ðŸ§¾ Where It Affects

| **Area**                          | **Impact**                                             |
| --------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------ |
| **Stock Ledger**                  | Determines the cost of each stock movement (in/out).   |
| **Stock Balance Report**          | Changes item valuation and total stock worth.          |
| **Accounting (COGS & Inventory)** | Impacts expense and asset valuation in General Ledger. |




