2. learn more about UOM ( Unit of Measure )
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”

Enabled :
- If checked â†’ this UOM can be used in transactions.
- Helps you disable any unused UOM without deleting it


UOM Name :
- The actual name of the unit (e.g., Nos, Kg, Meter, Box, Litre).
- Defines how quantity is measured across Buying, Selling, and Inventory.

Must be Whole Number :
- If checked â†’ quantity must be whole (no decimals).
- Used when partial quantity doesnâ€™t make sense (like Nos or Pieces). Example: canâ€™t buy 1.5 chairs


| **UOM Name**           | **Meaning / Used For**                                      | **Example Use Case**                           |
| ---------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------- |
| **Nos** (Numbers)      | Count of individual items.                                  | Chairs, Mobile Phones, Laptops (e.g., 10 Nos). |
| **Box**                | Used when items are packed in boxes.                        | 1 Box = 10 Bottles or 1 Box = 50 Units.        |
| **Kg** (Kilogram)      | For measuring weight in kilograms.                          | Sugar, Cement, Steel Rods, Vegetables.         |
| **Gram** (g)           | Smaller weight unit.                                        | Jewelry, Medicine, or Spices.                  |
| **Litre** (Ltr)        | For liquid items.                                           | Oil, Milk, Paint.                              |
| **Meter** (m)          | For measuring length.                                       | Cloth, Cable, Pipe.                            |
| **Centimeter** (cm)    | Smaller unit for length.                                    | Wire, Rope.                                    |
| **Square Meter** (sqm) | For area-based measurement.                                 | Tiles, Flooring, Fabric rolls.                 |
| **Cubic Meter** (cum)  | For volume-based measurement.                               | Sand, Concrete, Water Tank capacity.           |
| **Pair**               | Used for two-piece items.                                   | Shoes, Gloves, Socks.                          |
| **Packet** (Pkt)       | Packaged items in small quantities.                         | Snacks, Medicine Strips.                       |
| **Set**                | A combination of items.                                     | Tool Sets, Furniture Sets.                     |
| **Roll**               | Items that come in rolls.                                   | Fabric, Paper Roll, Wire Roll.                 |
| **Hour**               | For time-based services.                                    | Labor charge, Machine usage, Consultant fees.  |
| **Day**                | For service durations.                                      | Room booking, Vehicle rental.                  |
| **Piece**              | Similar to Nos â€” used interchangeably for individual items. | Furniture, Toys.                               |


