3. Auto re-order ( item -> inventory )
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”

| **Field Name**            | **Simple Meaning / Use**                                                                                                      |
| ------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Check in (Group)**      | ERPNext checks the stock level in this warehouse (or warehouse group) to see if it falls below the reorder level.             |
| **Request For**           | ERPNext will create a Material Request for this warehouse, meaning the new stock will be requested for this warehouse         |
                              (not sent automatically, just requested).                                                                                     |
| **Re-order Level**        | The **minimum stock quantity** at which ERPNext will **auto-create a Material Request**.                                      |
| **Re-order Qty**          | The **quantity to request/purchase** when stock goes below the Re-order Level.                                                |
| **Material Request Type** | Defines **what kind of Material Request** to create automatically (like *Purchase*, *Material Transfer*, or *Manufacture*).   |


âš™ï¸ Simple Example

| **Scenario**                     | **Explanation**                                                        |
| -------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Re-order Level = 10              | When stock goes below **10 units**, ERPNext will trigger auto-reorder. |
| Re-order Qty = 5                 | The system will create a Material Request for **5 units**.             |
| Material Request Type = Purchase | The request will be sent to the **Buying Module** for **purchase**.    |





