4. valuation rate in Item
->

It is the default cost ERPNext uses to calculate stock value when no other valuation data exists.



âœ… Where is Valuation Rate used?

ERPNext uses the valuation rate for:

1. Opening stock entries
- When you create an Opening Stock Entry, ERPNext takes valuation rate Ã— quantity to calculate opening stock value.

2. First purchase or manufacturing entry
- If no purchase history exists, the system uses the valuation rate.

3. Stock Ledger Valuation
- It is used in FIFO, Average, or Moving Average costing to compute the value of inventory.

4. Stock Reconciliation
- If a reconciliation is done without entering a rate, valuation rate is applied.



ðŸ“Œ Important note

Valuation rate in the Item master is not always the actual stock valuation.
Once your system has transactions, ERPNext starts calculating valuation rate automatically based on:
Purchase Receipt rates
Stock entries
Manufacturing cost
Additional costs (Landed Cost Voucher)

So the Itemâ€™s valuation rate is mostly used: ðŸ‘‰ Only as a starting value, not the ongoing valuation.



ðŸŽ¯ Example

If Item X has valuation rate = 100 INR
And you add opening stock of 10 qty:

Stock Value = 10 Ã— 100 = 1000 INR

Later if you purchase at 120, the valuation rate will be updated automatically.

in short,
Valuation Rate = Default cost of the item used to calculate inventory value until real transactions set the cost.



